{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"b33ri1rqronl2nwdgz4cs93","title":"Managerialism","desc":"","updated":1655451183616,"created":1655441183942,"tags":"political-science","custom":{},"fname":"concepts.managerialism","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Dendron"},"contentHash":"c78f9860b66f377c81f78bdcfd5cf584","links":[{"type":"frontmatterTag","from":{"fname":"concepts.managerialism","id":"b33ri1rqronl2nwdgz4cs93","vaultName":"Dendron"},"value":"tags.political-science","alias":"political-science","xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"tags.political-science"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"concepts.managerialism","id":"b33ri1rqronl2nwdgz4cs93","vaultName":"Dendron"},"value":"people.burnham","alias":"James Burnham's","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":18,"offset":18},"end":{"line":2,"column":52,"offset":52},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"people.burnham"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"concepts.managerialism","id":"b33ri1rqronl2nwdgz4cs93","vaultName":"Dendron"},"value":"concepts.ussr.nomenklatura","alias":"concepts.ussr.nomenklatura","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":273,"offset":682},"end":{"line":4,"column":303,"offset":712},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"concepts.ussr.nomenklatura"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"concepts.managerialism","id":"b33ri1rqronl2nwdgz4cs93","vaultName":"Dendron"},"value":"concepts.usa.brain-trust","alias":"concepts.usa.brain-trust","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":364,"offset":773},"end":{"line":4,"column":392,"offset":801},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"concepts.usa.brain-trust"}}],"anchors":{},"children":[],"parent":"4zumv5du4dtnq25bkcd3mua","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"managerialism\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#managerialism\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Managerialism</h1>\n<p>Managerialism is <a href=\"/notes/txeuhmj9btt7eeacpabbwlc\">James Burnham's</a> term to refer to the form of government adopted in the early 1900s by the Soviet Union, Nazi Germany, and the USA (to a lesser extent), replacing both capitalism and Lenin's attempt at socialism. To Burnham, each country had created a bureaucratic, technocratic class that was increasingly taking over the economy and displacing the previous ruling elite.</p>\n<p>This formulation, to Burnham, explains the tendencies of each nation better than their nominal form. While each of these nations maintained a public visage of ideological support for what preceded it, the actual practice in each case tended to be remarkably similar â€” the <a href=\"/notes/1u199zpdox1kdlr6st920rh\">nomenklatura</a> in the USSR, the rule of the Party in Nazi Germany, and the <a href=\"/notes/391u2mv3s0ofjqrfokyxmr2\">Brain Trust</a> in the United States.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"tags\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#tags\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Tags</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">political-science (Private)</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"tivrplnoaurusggrx2rxbz3","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1655447154745,"created":1655447154745,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Dendron"},"contentHash":"5040b8f2be19101555c72202ffe6ef73","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-dendron":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to Dendron","value":"welcome-to-dendron","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"lookup":{"type":"header","text":"Lookup","value":"lookup","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["93idrc5io9c85mw1ch3eooa","7zhpza84ga8jyyd1xpxsnbg","4zumv5du4dtnq25bkcd3mua","pfam485yk5ri9kp8mibo24c","vd78yqi2almdfr0jw4es92s","obo5p9dvn9q22hq29opjouw","aa71ue2uz5molq0hak6s141","f54pjw8wg5b81lkqpzkvq9w"